{
  "message": "feat(agent-drivers): scaffold AgentDriver abstraction + driver namespaces\n\nCreates the workspace package that will host Flywheel Gateway\u2019s \u201cAgent Driver\u201d abstraction.\n\nContext\n- The architecture explicitly supports multiple execution backends (SDK, ACP, Tmux) behind a single `AgentDriver` interface.\n- Establishing the package boundary early prevents app code from coupling directly to any one backend.\n\nWhat\u2019s included\n- `packages/agent-drivers/src/interface.ts`\n  - `AgentDriverType` union (`'sdk' | 'acp' | 'tmux' | 'mock'`).\n  - Minimal `AgentDriver` interface surface (identity + type) to be expanded as lifecycle/tool/event APIs are implemented.\n- Driver namespaces (placeholders) for the planned backends:\n  - `src/sdk/*` (primary: structured SDK events)\n  - `src/acp/*` (JSON-RPC stdio / IDE-compat)\n  - `src/tmux/*` (power-user fallback)\n\nWhy this commit is \u201csmall\u201d\n- This is intentionally a contract + directory scaffold only.\n- Real driver behavior (spawn/send/subscribe, tool-call routing, terminal attach, capabilities) should be implemented incrementally alongside the driver beads so we don\u2019t accidentally commit to premature API shapes.",
